column1: 1/ Real personal income for metropolitan areas is personal income divided by the RPPs and the national PCE price index. The result is a chained dollar estimate of real personal income, in thousands of chained 2012 dollars. Statistics presented in thousands of dollars do not indicate more precision than statistics presented in millions of dollars.
2/ Real per capita personal income is total real personal income divided by total midyear population.
3/ Real personal income for the United States Nonmetropolitan Portion was estimated using multiple statistical area delineations published by the Office of Management and Budget (OMB).
4/ Real personal income estimates are not available for Enid, OK prior to 2013, Twin Falls, ID prior to 2015, and Poughkeepsie-Newburgh-Middletown, NY prior to 2016.
Last updated: December 15, 2020-- new statistics for 2019; revised statistics for 2017-2018.
